President Biden spoke at the East Room to thank the Senate for confirming his historic and diverse Cabinet. He announced that he has asked five Cabinet members, Pete Buttigieg, Jennifer Granholm, Marcia Fudge, Marty Walsh, and Gina Raimondo, to take on the task of explaining and selling his American Jobs program to the public. Additionally, he emphasized his commitment to Buy American and directed every member of the Cabinet to ensure their agency's spending aligns with his Buy American standard. President Biden concluded by stating that there is a lot of business to be done and thanked the press for their presence.